<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Calling strncpy(ldev->dev_name, dev_name, sizeof(ldev->dev_name) - 1) can read up to sizeof(ldev->dev_name)-1 bytes from the source pointer dev_name. If dev_name does not point to a null-terminated string (or points into a smaller object than sizeof(ldev->dev_name)-1), strncpy may read past the bounds of the object referenced by dev_name, causing an out‑of‑bounds access.
